				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Newbie here!<a name="35744"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 21 04 12:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi all, I'm a newbie bard and EQer learning to play with the guidance of my bf who has played for several years. Without him, I don't think I'd be nearly as far along as I am now - which isn't all that far! 
<br />

<br />
I have a few questions, and while I fully believe one should search the entire forum before asking, I can't seem to always understand the lingo.
<br />

<br />
Let's start with me: Just lvl'd to 15 last night. I'm a half-elf with some pretty good gear, playing on The Rathe. I run around East Commons &amp; North Ro for the most part, but recently started dying...er playing in Oasis.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
My main question for now is at a lvl 15, which songs should be my &quot;Must Haves&quot;? I solo some, but I really like to pull. Primarily I'm using Regn, Anthem, Bellow, and Resist (poison/magic, etc). I usually target a mob, then bellow and run back to my group. I'll twist the other songs (regen, anthem, and resist) and sometimes I'll hit too. 
<br />

<br />
Since I like to pull a lot, how can I use lull, bellow, and mez? If I'm soloing, should I use lull to pull one mob? If so, am I supposed to lull all the mobs except the one I want?
<br />

<br />
And my last question is, how does the Charsima song help me? I've used it on a vendor, but it doesn't seem to help.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
{Surion - 15 Bard }</span></td>
