			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="35806"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 21 04 3:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;Must Haves&quot;? 
<br />

<br />
All bard questions can be answered with &quot;It depends&quot; because bards are so versatile.  In your case, it depends on your group, what you are fighting and what your role is.  That being said, you will prolly always want Hymn (regen), Anthem, Selo's (speed), Bellow &amp; Mez.  Add Lull whenever you will be pulling and resistances depending on targets.  Having speed is not only good for travel and long pulls but also for some escapes.
<br />

<br />
It has been some time since I was 15 (grats btw), but here are my recommendations for pulling at that level (your mileage may vary):
<br />

<br />
Assuming your group consists of at least one healer type and one main tank (depending on gear you may be able to fill the tank role), let's assume you are facing 4 mobs.  Hopefully you have a key set up for both Cycle Target and Toggle Target. 
<br />

<br />
Eventually, you will be able to pull all 4 mobs, let the main tank take one and you keep the other 3 locked down by cycling mez.  You can even engage in melee while doing this if you are careful.  After the first dies, you can add another song in to replace the mez you no longer have to do (probably anthem, hymn or bellow).  Continue this til the last one when you can twist your main 3 (or 4 if you are so inclined and have a good connection).  Learning to handle 4 mobs at a time will serve you well in later levels and will probably increase your groups' kill rate.  
<br />

<br />
And until you are comfortable with that many at one time or if your group can't handle that many, use lull to decrease the number you have to deal with.  Remember that lull doesnt remove aggro, it just decreases the range of aggro so dont pull a mob thru a lulled mob and expect it to stay lulled.
<br />

<br />
And another note on the Charisma song, it is known to work on some vendors and not on others.  You can check by &quot;con'ing&quot; them before and after you cast the song on them to see if it's having any effect.  For example, if you are &quot;indifferent&quot; to Izbal Brightblaze in Butcherblock, this song will raise you to &quot;amiable&quot;.
<br />

<br />
Happy hunting and welcome.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
