				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="36562"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 26 04 5:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The solution to your instrument-swapping problem is PRIMARY equippable instruments.  Depending on your budget, here are some suggestions:
<br />

<br />
Wind:
<br />

<br />
Ivory Horn (1.8 mod, drops off big bugs in Shar Vahl and Shadeweavers.  Should be DIRT cheap.)
<br />
Bloodstained Flute (2.2 mod, should be pretty cheap, common drop in LDoN stuff.  I use this at lvl 59!)
<br />

<br />
Percussion:
<br />

<br />
Truborn Drum of Dark Rites (2.6 mod, LDoN drop, should run a few hundred PP.  An excellent value)
<br />
Thunderous Drum of Karana (2.8 mod.  This drum kicks a$.  Get one by lvl 30 if you can.  Don't pay over 10k, try for 5k or less)
<br />

<br />
Brass:
<br />

<br />
A Flawless Ivory Horn (2.0 mod, drops off same bugs as Ivory Horn)
<br />
Troubador's Mace (1.8 mod, 1 hand basher.  Try to get one by lvl 42.  Try not to pay more than 5k)
<br />

<br />
String:
<br />

<br />
This is the bugger.  Perhaps the easiest PRIMARY String to accquire is the Lost Explorer's Lute, purchased from Guk LDoN camp for 52 points.
<br />

<br />
Lute of the Howler (2.2 mod)  This is a VERY cool item with a warewolf illusion / buff clicky.  Thus it is almost always ridiculously priced.  Coolness factor is off the charts though, and the clicky buff is AWESOME when you are midlevels.  (Higher levels, your songs are better, hehe)
<br />

<br />
Rajurkian Lute of Battle is awesome, with a 2.6 mod.  Problem is, it costs 510 adventure points at the EC camp...
<br />

<br />
Fortunately, the most frequent use of String is for regen songs between fights, so the three clicks vs. one click to equip is not SO bad.  As an avid instrument twister though, I can tell you that I longed for a Primary Lute for a LONG time, and finally have one.  It is my pride and joy!
<br />

<br />
I believe the Song of Travel on the BP you mentioned is a clicky effect.  I'm sure, however, that like the Singing Steel stuff, there is a minimum level at which you can click it.</span></td>
