				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="36702"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 10:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When I was lvl 15, all I had were my store bought standard instruments, and just like you, I wondered how I could find a way around switching them out all the time, because even if you have your hot buttons set up to make switching easier, it can become a real drag. Eventually (not anytime soon) you will be shooting for having as many instrument mods in armor and weapons as possible, this way you don't have to switch out anything unless you're kiting one way or another. Klap's info is awesome, I just want to give my own insight on the subject too:
<br />
IMO the first item you should try to get your hands on is a Troubador's Mace (Brass instruments), so keep practicing 1HB skills and make sure you don't let it fall behind! The mace should hang out in your offhand because it's slower. After the mace, look for a Gem Inlaid Longsword, this has decent stats and gives a somewhat weak Percussion mod. I used this is my main hand and mace in offhand from 25-44. When running and soloing I still used the Thunderous Drums because of the mod, but in combat the Gem Inlaid Longsword is GREAT. You should not have to pay more than 5k for each of these. Keep your piercing skills maxed because later I reccommend you replace the Gem Inlaid Longsword with a Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche. Click on the thing in my sig that says &quot;check me out!&quot; and take a look at the weapons, it might help. There is armor out there, and augments you can get from LDoN with more instrument mods, and it is a good idea to try and aim for getting as many mods on your regular items as possible without having to switch items. 
<br />
Anyways I hope that wasn't too much babbling, take care and keep at it!
<br />
