		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="36815"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 4:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">How do those work? What's it mean, 'Clickable'? Would it be something like setting up a hotkey to select my breastplate for example? I'm just wondering... 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
There are different types of &quot;effects&quot; on items.  Some say (combat) next to the effect name.  That is what we call a &quot;proc&quot; (processing).  That means that while you are hitting a mob with the OMG Longsword of Everything Slaying, there is a random chance that the effect, Holy Crap Nuke of Death, might go off.  That chance is increased by having higher Dexterity.  Most of these items also have a minimum level at which they will &quot;proc&quot;.
<br />

<br />
Some effects are what we call &quot;clickies&quot;.  That means that you right click the item to activate it, and the casting bar comes up, like a song or spell.  (Some are instant, which is most kewl).  You must stop singing, btw, to &quot;cast&quot; the effect.  Now, some say &quot;(must equip)&quot; next to the effect.  That means that you have to be WEARING the item to clickie it (like Singing Steel Armor effects).  Others can simply be in an inventory slot (like the Mask of Deception-- makes you a Dark Elf!).  Again, many of these have minimum levels at which you can activate them.  I believe they added the minimum levels to the item descriptions with the recent patch.  (It used to be you just had to &quot;know&quot; a lot of stuff, like Haste percentages, Instrument Modifiers, Proc Levels etc. , look it up online, or ask around for someone who knew.)
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, there is no way to get a &quot;clicky&quot; effect mapped to your keyboard.  You can only do it using the mouse.  You CAN, however, have the inventory slot the item is in displayed in your hotkey bank, so you don't have to open your inventory screen to activate it.  To do that, you left-click and hold the inventory slot you want in your hotkey bank until it pops onto your cursor.  Then pop it into the hotkey slot you want.  (You can, btw, put a bag in a hotkey slot, and hitting that hotkey WILL open it for you.  You just can't activate a &quot;clicky&quot; with the hotkey itself.  You still have to right click it with your mouse in the hotkey slot.)
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Tonight I'm going to set up spell sheets. I'm assuming I should make one for Solo and one for Pulling? Any others?</span></blockquote>
<br />
With higher levels, and more variety of song selection and solo methods, you may have LOTS of spellsets.  Among mine at lvl 60 are:  ChantKite, AE, SwarmKite, WithShammy, SlowHaste, Resist, RaidBuff etc.
<br />

<br />
When you set up spellsets, one tip to keep in mind.  One great advantage of them, is the speed with which you can mem new spells.  For example, I was in a group that all-but wiped.  (Necro Feigned Death, I ran like h*ll, lmao).  Well, I was able to run away from the mobs, rightclick my spell book, and memorize my ChantKite spellset before the mobs got to me and killed me.  Then I was able to chant them all down.  (Was funny.  When the group got back and started rezzing, I was still running in circles on kill number 7 or so, lmao.)
<br />

<br />
The key to quick spellset memming is having the SAME songs in the SAME song slots as much as possible.  When you mem a songlist, the songs are mapped to the specific slot you put them in.  Thus, if you have Selos in slot 7, and your songlist has it in slot 8, it will RE-MEMORIZE Selos into slot 8, taking more time.  If you ALWAYS have Selos, Heal, whatever, in the SAME slot, you will NOT have to re-memorize those songs to mem your songlist.  Only the ones that weren't common to both lists have to be re-memmed.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
