			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="36824"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 4:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">because even if you have your hot buttons set up to make switching easier, it can become a real drag.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is still a skill you should develop. The majority of instrument mods on weapons/armor are 1.8 or 2.0; these are easily outstripped by actual instruments. (LDoN augs are generally 1.4-1.8.) There are a few augs/weapons/armor that are 2.5 or higher, if you're lucky, but the vast majority are the equivalent of storebought instruments or worse.
<br />

<br />
Your haste might not get an instrument modifier, but STR/ATK bonuses do, your chant damage does, and there's a point when switching real instruments might increase your group's damage noticeably more than you meleeing or just sitting there with your LDoN augs.
<br />

<br />
I'm not saying you're ALWAYS going to need to do this, but there might come a time when it's helpful.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I don't actually use my hotkeys to switch instruments (I use my hotkeys to twist). I have a GUI mod that gives me convenient inventory slots on my main window. If you don't want to make one yourself, there's a ton available for download at www.eqinterface.com.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
