				<td colspan="2"><span>Surion,
<br />

<br />
Keep at it.  In a couple more levels you will start to get songs that will change the way you play.  When you get charm and furfils you and your BL bf can start to charm duo.  It will take some doing but you will figure it out.  Read all the guides on soloing and then add a BL and adapt.  Dont forget to group and dont forget to have fun<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Some tips that have helped me:
<br />

<br />
1) get a custom UI  Keiz is good and he supports it on this site in a forum <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=16066">here</a>.  You can download it at www.eqinterface.com.
<br />
2) in addition to spell sheets I save partial sheets.  If you leave the spell gem empty it doesnt replace the spell.  This lets me define a couple of utility spell gems and quickly swap them out.  I use it if a dispell or aria is needed in a hurry.
<br />
3)SOW Potions.  When you solo, these can make life a lot easier and less risky.
<br />
4)Tank when you can at these lower levels.  It will raise your defence with less risk.  You dont have to endanger your group - just take your share of the beating<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />
It sounds like you have learned the other lessions like know your songs and dont panic.  Keep up the good work. 
<br />

<br />
Also I love your pictures.
<br />

