				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Newbie here!<a name="40682"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 19 04 7:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">but I don't understand what this is all about. Does this mean I can mem more than 8 songs?</span></blockquote>
<br />
These are the spell effects that affect you.  The big box is for regular spells.  The small box is for your bard songs (although some songs end up in the big box - I dont know why).
<br />

<br />
Also, SOW potions are sold by players in the bazaar.  I use them when I solo as kind of a safty net.
<br />

<br />
Soloing the 30s-40s are probably our best soloing times because so much of the content is soloable.
<br />

<br />
Fear Kiting: sing snare (lvl 23) fear (lvl 26) and beat the mob to death as it flees slowly.  Your fear song can cause adds so you have to time your fear correctly to avoid them.  This is the slowest kite style.
<br />

<br />
Swarm kiting - where you get a pack, charm one, then let the pack beat it down until its almost dead, break charm, then chant your former pet dead - is fun, often exciting and great experience.  Unlike fear kiting you will kill things very fast &lt; 1 min per kill.  It does get old however.  
<br />

<br />
AOE Kiting - Gather up EVERYTHING and run in a pattern so your AOE songs hit the mobs but they dont hit you.  Unlike swarming you are killing everything at once.  It may take 10-15 minutes but you can kill 30+ mobs.  People who do it say it is great.  I never got the hang of it.  I guess I hate dying too much.
<br />

<br />
There are great guides for soloing (I'm sure you know that).  Experiement and have fun.  Dont forget to group too<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />
Tin.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
