				<td colspan="2"><span>Woohoo I got the top half of Page 24 last night! I started my night by switching computers from my laptop to a desktop. This always takes a while for me to get it set up the way I like. I added <a href="http://www.eqinterface.com/sdownload/picture.php?s=&amp;id=1056">this mod</a> to my UI and wow did it ever help my instrument switching! I made a few song sheets and while I was trying to figure out why my maps were screwy (had the height filter on) someone buffed the bejeezes out of me. Perfect time to practice fear/snare just outside of the spires in splitpaw.
<br />

<br />
I decided that wouldn't work with the gnolls because they'd head for their friends and I'd have more trouble. I decided to kite by twisting regen, selos, and DDD while playing my brass and running in a circle. 
<br />

<br />
The circle thing is rough. I bumped into a few trees and got hit quite a bit. Since I was just practicing with 1 mob at a time, the time it took to kite didn't outweigh the experience. I want to practice that some more.
<br />

<br />
Just keep in mind that you shouldn't try to kite archers. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the info on the UIs. I was looking for a way to organize my screen better since it seemed hard to see sometimes, but I think I have it figured out now.
